title: What can I do if my phone fails to access the Internet?
answer: [Insert a SIM card into your phone. The phone then automatically configures APN settings.]() [To view the APN settings, go to Settings > Wireless & networks > Access Point Names.]() If the parameter settings are incorrect, touch ![](http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=111725). From the displayed option menu, choose Reset to default.
